                    <head type="stepTitle" xml:lang="en">Part-of-speech tagging</head>
                    <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en">Part-of-speech tagging (POS or PoS
                        tagging) refers to assigning grammatical information to the units of the
                        text. There are defined tagsets commonly used for individual languages or
                        language groups.Particularly noteworthy is the Universal Dependencies (UD)
                        initiative which aims at mapping the idiosyncratic tagsets to one harmonized
                        vocabulary/tagset. Most current tools used for PoS tagging rely on machine
                        learning technologies. </desc>
